Analysts have welcomed Finance Minister Tito Mboweni's unexpected release of an economic strategy for the country. JOHANNESBURG - Analysts have welcomed Finance Minister Tito Mboweni's unexpected release of an economic strategy for the country. The plan proposes reviewing regulations on everything from fuel to banking and suggests ways to get more tourists and immigrants into the country. Treasury's strategy document may hold the answer to economic growth and job creation if it gets off the ground. It's more focused than previous revival plans. READ: Mboweni's plan to save economy Some of the key proposals include: On electricity, the document suggests households should be able to sell electricity they generate from solar panels. The strategy document is also making some bold proposals on Eskom. Finance Minister Tito Mboweni has released his economic plan, titled Economic Transformation, Inclusive Growth and Competitiveness Towards an Economic Strategy for South Africa.